 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Due to the prior knowledge and sequence data for a range of stress response genes in 
  <span class="italic">A. millepora</span>, the already published transcriptome data set [
  <a ref-type="bibr" rid="B51" href="#B51">51</a>] from larvae collected at Magnetic Island, an small inshore island in the central GBR, was downloaded and mined for SNPs using PipeMeta as above. A selection of nine genes was made, based on published information relating to thermal stress responses and SNP information derived from the transcriptome sequence data [
  <a ref-type="bibr" rid="B51" href="#B51">51</a>] (Table 
  <a ref-type="table" rid="T2" href="#T2">2</a>). For each gene, one suitable, non-synonymous SNP site was chosen to be used on the GBR wide sample set (Table 
  <a ref-type="table" rid="T2" href="#T2">2</a>). 
 </p>
